Path Compression in find

Union by Rank or Union by Size`

The amortized time complexity per operation is:

O(Î±(n))

Which means:

n operations take about O(n Â· Î±(n)) â‰ˆ O(n) time in practice.

âœ… Inverse Ackermann Function (Î±(n))
Î±(n) is the inverse of that function.

It answers: â€œHow many times do we need to apply the inverse Ackermann function to reduce n to a small constant?â€

ðŸ”¸ In practice, Î±(n) â‰¤ 5 for all reasonable n (n â‰¤ 2^65536)

So, for any real-world size input â€” even billions â€”

âœ… O(Î±(n)) behaves like constant time.


Feature	DFS-Based	DSU-Based
Time Complexity	O(n + m)	O(n + m) (with Î±(n) factor)
Space Complexity	O(n + m)	O(n)
Practical Speed	Slower for sparse graphs	Faster due to constant-time unions
Implementation Ease	Simpler	Slightly more complex
